    <name>◤ F — NIGERIA NON-KINETIC STABILITY LAYER</name>
    <open>0</open>
    <description><![CDATA[Governance/security reform, judicial accountability, FX/fiscal capacity, and social-pressure markers — the stability counterweight to the kinetic Nigeria picture.]]></description>
    <Placemark>
      <name>About this layer</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Purpose:</b> Separate non-kinetic state-stability indicators from attack / insurgency mapping.<br/>
<b>Categories:</b><br/>
- Governance / security reform (green)<br/>
- Political / judicial / corruption risk (pink)<br/>
- Economic / energy / FX / fiscal capacity (yellow)<br/>
- Social pressure / labor / service delivery (white)<br/><br/>
<b>Use:</b> Overlay this on top of conflict maps to track whether the Nigerian state is stabilizing, fragmenting, or merely firefighting.]]></description>
